When compiling software such as with the gcc compiler, which of the following is therecommended name for a file containing commands and relationships used with themake command?
A)  Makefile
B)  makefile
C)  make.file
D)  Makefile.txt
A
A. According to the man(1) page for the make command, the name Makefile, withan uppercase M, is the recommended name for the file. The name makefile is validas a default but is not the recommended option. The other options are not valid asdefault names.
